The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It specifically focuses on auctions (cs.DS) and considers objectives such as welfare and revenue, which are common in algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms (cs.EC) and the regularity assumption on the distribution, which is a common topic in statistical learning theory (cs.LG).
